					<description><![CDATA[<p>San Francisco-based startup Eigen has emerged from stealth with a different ambition: using artificial intelligence to make people more human. The firm said today that it has completed a $15</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/eigen-secures-15m-seed-for-mutual-friend-ai-tool/" data-wpel-link="internal">Eigen Secures $15M Seed for ‘Mutual Friend’ AI Tool</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">San Francisco-based startup </span><a href="https://github.com/PX4/eigen" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Eigen </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has emerged from stealth with a different ambition: using artificial intelligence to make people more human. The firm said today that it has completed a $15 million seed round of </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/plata-raises-405m-hits-5b-valuation-in-fintech-boom/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">to build its leading platform, which it calls the world&#8217;s first &#8220;mutual friend&#8221; AI.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by Benchmark, one of the most influential venture firms in the space, which was an early investor in social platforms like eBay, Twitter, and Uber. A slew of high-profile angel investors also participated, including Ben Silbermann (co-founder of Pinterest), Gustavo Söderström (co-president of Spotify), Kothari, Akshay (co-founder of Notion), David Singleton (CTO of Stripe), and Will Wu (ex-product lead at Snap).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Moving Beyond the &#8220;Chatbot&#8221; Era</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Eigen, founded in 2025 by </span><b>Paul Scherer</b><span style="font-weight: 400">, is positioning its technology as a corrective to the &#8220;lonely&#8221; trajectory of modern AI. While most generative AI today focuses on one-on-one interactions, such as personal assistants or romantic chatbots, Eigen’s “Mutual Friend” is designed to act as a social bridge between real people.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200158" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200158" class="size-large wp-image-200158" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/AI-Representation-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="AI Representation" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-200158" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“We believe the next frontier of AI isn’t about building a better robot to talk to; it’s about using intelligence to help us belong and grow together,” said Scherer, who famously left school at 16 to pursue coding before relocating from Germany to San Francisco. “A mutual friend in the real world helps you find common ground, breaks the ice, and deepens your existing bonds. That is exactly what we are building digitally.”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/plata-raises-405m-hits-5b-valuation-in-fintech-boom/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> Plata Raises $405M, Hits $5B Valuation in Fintech Boom</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">How the &#8220;Mutual Friend&#8221; Works</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While the company has kept specific interface details under wraps during its stealth phase, the core philosophy centers on </span><b>pro-social AI</b><span style="font-weight: 400">. The tool is designed to integrate into existing social and professional circles to:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Identify Shared Growth Areas</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Recommending joint tasks or shared learning paths based on a group&#8217;s collaborative interests.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Enable synchronous experiences</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: shifting from social media doomscrolling to active, shared encounters both digitally and physically.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400"><strong>Emotional Intelligence (EQ) Building</strong>: Furnishing the context and information that allows interaction participants to manage even complicated social exchanges in the absence of human-to-human dialogue.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A High-Stakes Bet on Connection</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $15 million seed round is notably large for an initial capital raise, even by 2026 standards, signalling intense investor confidence in Scherer’s vision. Benchmark’s involvement is particularly telling; the firm rarely leads seed rounds unless it sees potential for a massive, category-defining shift in how humans interact.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industry analysts suggest that Eigen is tapping into a growing &#8220;tech-backlash&#8221; sentiment. As social isolation reaches record highs despite, or perhaps because of, digital connectivity, there is a massive market for tools that facilitate genuine human-to-human relationships rather than human-to-machine ones.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With the new capital, Eigen plans to expand its small, elite team of engineers and social scientists to refine its emotional intelligence models and prepare for a broader public rollout later this year.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/eigen-secures-15m-seed-for-mutual-friend-ai-tool/" data-wpel-link="internal">Eigen Secures $15M Seed for ‘Mutual Friend’ AI Tool</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
