					<description><![CDATA[<p>TextQL, the AI-native analytics platform, announced it has raised $17 million in a strategic funding round. Blackstone Innovations Investments (BXII), Blackstone’s early-stage arm, anchored the investment. A massive wave of</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/textql-raises-17m-to-transform-enterprise-data-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal">TextQL Raises $17M to Transform Enterprise Data Intelligence</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://textql.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">TextQL</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, the AI-native analytics platform, announced it has raised $17 million in a strategic </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/plata-raises-405m-hits-5b-valuation-in-fintech-boom/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. </span>Blackstone Innovations Investments (BXII), Blackstone’s early-stage arm, anchored the investment. A massive wave of enterprise interest in AI agents drives the funding. TextQL designed its flagship AI agent, Ana, to act as a virtual data scientist. Ana replaces the traditional three-week data request cycle with 90-second automated answers.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Messy Data&#8221; Problem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While large language models (LLMs) like GPT-4 have proven capable of writing basic SQL, they often struggle in the complex, &#8220;noisy&#8221; environments of major corporations. TextQL differentiates itself by focusing on the metadata and context layer—the connective tissue between a company’s raw data warehouse and its business logic.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200145" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200145" class="size-full wp-image-200145" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/TextQL.jpg" alt="TextQL Logo" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-200145" class="wp-caption-text">Source: TextQL</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Enterprises are done trying to force AI into systems that were never designed for it,&#8221; said Ethan Ding, CEO and co-founder of TextQL. &#8220;They want a data warehouse that assumes AI agents are first-class actors. We’ve been building this from the beginning. Now we scale it.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Instead of requiring human analysts to manually map every table, TextQL’s platform automatically indexes relationships across disparate systems, including Snowflake, BigQuery, dbt, and Looker. This creates a shared knowledge layer that allows Ana to reason over raw data with a level of &#8220;deterministic, auditable accuracy&#8221; that traditional LLMs lack.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/plata-raises-405m-hits-5b-valuation-in-fintech-boom/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Plata Raises $405M, Hits $5B Valuation in Fintech Boom</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Validation from the World’s Largest Asset Manager</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The involvement of Blackstone is more than just a financial boost; it is a significant technological endorsement. Blackstone, which manages over $1 trillion in assets, operates some of the most complex data environments in existence. According to TextQL, Blackstone’s CTO, John Stecher, noted that the platform provided &#8220;one of the fastest times-to-value&#8221; he has seen for AI operating over complex data.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">TextQL&#8217;s footprint is already expansive. The company revealed that its systems are live at major organizations like Dropbox, where Ana queries across more than 400,000 tables and 100,000 dashboards. Other notable clients include Scale AI and companies within the healthcare vertical, where TextQL agents are used to reconcile data across EHRs (Electronic Health Records) and pharmacy systems.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Road Ahead: From Chat to Autonomy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With the fresh $17 million in capital, TextQL plans to accelerate the development of its &#8220;agentic analytics&#8221; infrastructure. </span>This includes expanding its Sandcastles technology and refining its Playbooks, which let AI agents run autonomous reports and checks.</p>
<p>Ethan Ding and Mark Hay founded the company in 2022, and it has seen explosive growth. The company reported a 9x year-over-year revenue increase and a net dollar retention rate exceeding 300%. This funding round positions TextQL as a frontrunner redefining how the world’s largest companies interact with their information.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/textql-raises-17m-to-transform-enterprise-data-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal">TextQL Raises $17M to Transform Enterprise Data Intelligence</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
